<div id="outline-container-the-state" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="the-state"><span class="section-number-2">4</span> The State</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-the-state">
<p>
What is a state? &gt; a state is a human community that (successfully)
claims the monopoly of the legitimate use of physical force within a
given territory
</p>

<p>
Where do states come from?
</p>

<p>
<b>Social contract theory:</b> &gt; The state rises from the cumulative
experience of a populations&#x2026;
</p>

<p>
Basically, the need for a leader / social contract arises with size.
</p>

<p>
<b>Bellicist theory:</b> with Charles Tilly &gt; war makes states and states
make war
</p>
</div>

